<br>
I made a tunic with about 3 tries. ran out for some more skins, i'm not even out of kelethin and someone starts inspecting me.<br>
/rude<br>
/run away<br>
<br>
It bothers me when people walk up to you and starting lookin at your stuff without permission.<br>
<br>
So the guy gives me a tell. "Whats ur prob?"<br>
"people inspecting me without asking"<br>
"chill out, i wanted 2 see what u got"<br>
"it's a freaking patwork tunic"<br>
"thx"<br>
<br>
My friend and guildmate Kheri has blue fine steel plate. I can understand if i was wearing some cool looking gear. But it was 1 patchwork tunic.<br>
<br>
So i run down, i'm fighting this wolf, and someone else come up and starts looking at my equip. I kill the wolf and /rude the person who is looking at me.<br>
"don't get so uptight, i just wanna see what ur using."<br>
<br>
I personally don't think it's anyones damn business what i'm wearing/wielding.<br>
<br>
I was inspected 12 times making a suit of patchwork. This doesn't happen to my ranger or druid. On the rare occasion that they get inspected it's always preceeded by, "can i check out your gear?"<br>
<br>
Is there somekind of influx of retarded people all of a sudden?<br>
<br>
I can't tell you how many times my little warrior dude gets KSed by some stupid wizard. It's always a wizard because the druids are busy trying to kite everything and necros don't usually venture near Kelethin.<br>
<br>
I'm whacking away at this orc, along comes "BOOM"<br>
an orc dies, and i don't get the xp.<br>
A wizard loots the corpse infront of me and says, "ur welcome" i ask, "for what" he says, "saving u! u were in trouble" and i said, "well gee, look at my health, pretty much near the top huh? thanks for killstealing and looting it infront of me! i really needed that! it's not like even if i did die, i wouldnt lose any XP and it's a 20 second walk from town!"<br>
"ur ungratefull, i'm never helpin u again, and i'm tellin my guild to not help u!"<br>
<br>
5, 6 times a night this happens, i can hardly level. People piss me off. This never happens to my ranger or druid...WHY to my little warrior who is just trying to survive?<br>
<br>
Did a whole bunch of retarded people buy the game? Did the level 60s decide to make new characters and out of some benevolent nature decide to "protect" all the newbies? <p><center><img src="http://uhavax.hartford.edu/~kerick/laesig.jpg"></center></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uamorene.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Amorene</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(3/9/01 4:59:39 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Jerks and Newbz Alike</span><hr size=1> Admittedly, I often inspect lower level characters without<br>
asking, usually when deciding whether or not to buff them<br>
without being asked or throw low level items like Axes of<br>
the Ironback or Bloodstained Tunics at them. It can be<br>
hard telling the difference between a banded and a fungi<br>
tunic from the player model, and while I have nothing<br>
against twinks per se, it gives me the warm fuzzies to give<br>
actual newbies items they can use. I always ask high level<br>
characters, and they always say yes, without exception.<br>
The only time I ever get peevish with being inspected is<br>
when its followed by &quot;Can you port me and a friend....&quot; <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udarladelicious.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Darla Delicious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(3/12/01 4:41:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> How does inspecting hurt you?</span><hr size=1> Other than seeing the &quot;--- is looking at your equipment&quot; line, someone inspecting you costs you no time.  <br>
<br>
I kinda like it when someone is impressed enough by my stuff that they want to see what it is.  Now, when it is followed by, &quot;Can I see that in the trade window?&quot; or &quot;What are the stats on your pants, arms, shield, whatever?&quot;, that pisses me off.  Except for sometimes when I'm at the bazaar or I'm obviously not busy, and then they better ask nicely.<br>
<br>
I also have been given items by higher lvl players, and I've given items away in turn.  And never asked if I could inspect.<br>
<br>
Honestly, I get so many tells in game, I get annoyed if someone sends me a tell asking to inspect me.  Don't bother me with that @#%$.....just look if you want.<br>
<br>
Darla Delicious<br>
42 Druid, High Council, The Nightmare Elite <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utallithainofthela.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tallithain of the LA</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(3/16/01 9:54:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: How does inspecting hurt you?</span><hr size=1> I figure staying away from the newbie areas helps a lot with this.  A lot of times I just camo myself so I don't stand out while heading in to do my banking.<br>
